  "prompt": "When the Night King's White Walkers take children, do they become fully grown like those at end of the Game of Thrones episode \"Oathbreaker?\"",
  "response": "Yes, in the **Game of Thrones** television series, when the Night King and the White Walkers capture children, those children are transformed into White Walkers who appear as fully grown adults. This transformation is evident in the episode titled \"**Oathbreaker**,\" where children taken by the White Walkers undergo a metamorphosis that not only changes their allegiance but also alters their physical appearance to match the imposing stature and features of existing White Walkers.\n\nThe process typically involves the Night King using his supernatural abilities to reanimate and transform the captured individuals. The resulting White Walkers possess enhanced strength, longevity, and other mystical attributes that distinguish them from regular humans. By transforming children into fully grown White Walkers, the Night King effectively expands his army with beings that are both formidable and loyal, furthering his agenda of spreading the endless night.\n\nThis depiction underscores the chilling efficiency and ruthlessness of the Night King, as he doesn't limit himself to reanimating the deceased but actively converts the living to bolster his ranks. The transformation of children into adult White Walkers serves as a powerful narrative tool to illustrate the pervasive and terrifying reach of the Night King's forces.",
